higdon <- function(x) {
  i <- which(x <= 0.6)
  x[i] <- 2 * sin(pi * 0.8 * x[i] * 4) + 0.4 * cos(pi * 0.8 * x[i] * 16)
  x[-i] <- 2 * x[-i] - 1
  return(x)
}

np <- 100
xp <- seq(0, 1, length = np)
yp <- higdon(xp)

f <- function(x) as.numeric(x > 0.5)

# Training data
x <- seq(0, 1, length = 8) 
y <- f(x)

# Testing data
xp <- seq(0, 1, length = 100)
yp <- f(xp)

plot(xp, yp, type = "l", col = 4, xlab = "X", ylab = "Y", main = "Step function")
